---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — MinimalDev"
  description="About MinimalDev: free online utility tools built for speed, clarity, and practical use."
  canonicalPath="/legal/about/"
>
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="page-title">About MinimalDev</h1>

    <section class="section">
      <p class="lead">
        MinimalDev is a collection of free online tools designed to solve small, practical problems quickly.
        The focus is on clarity, speed, and usability rather than complex interfaces or feature-heavy software.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>One tool per page</strong> so each task stays focused and easy to understand.</li>
        <li><strong>Simple UX</strong> with clear inputs and readable results.</li>
        <li><strong>Fast performance</strong> with minimal dependencies and lightweight code.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Purpose</h2>
      <p>
        The goal of this site is to provide quick-access tools for everyday use cases such as calculations,
        formatting, conversions, and small workflow tasks. Many of these tasks do not require full applications,
        but still benefit from a dedicated interface that gives immediate results.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Who it is for</h2>
      <p>
        MinimalDev is intended for general users, students, developers, and anyone who needs simple utilities
        for day-to-day tasks. The tools are designed to be usable without prior knowledge or setup.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>How tools are built</h2>
      <p>
        Each tool is designed as a standalone page with a specific purpose. The structure, inputs, and outputs
        are implemented intentionally rather than generated automatically as bulk content. The goal is to keep
        each page focused on one clear function so results are easier to understand.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Privacy and data handling</h2>
      <p class="note">
        Most tools run directly in your browser. We do not require accounts and we avoid collecting personal data
        unless explicitly stated on a specific tool page.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Maintenance and updates</h2>
      <p>
        Tools are reviewed and improved over time to ensure they remain accurate, usable, and consistent.
        Updates may include bug fixes, UI improvements, or adjustments based on real usage patterns.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p class="note">
        For feedback, suggestions, or issues, please use the <a href="/legal/contact/">Contact</a> page.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>